   "source": [
    "# Molecular dynamics\n",
    "\n",
    "The free particle is characterized for having no external potential goberning its motion. In the case of temperature and friction abscence the particle is moving in a uniform rectilineous trajectory. And when temperature and friction are present, we have nothing but a stochastic brownian particle or random walker characterized by magnitudes as diffusion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## With OpenMM\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "import openmm as mm\n",
    "from openmm import unit\n",
    "from uibcdf_systems import FreeParticle\n",
    "\n",
    "molecular_system = FreeParticle(n_particles=1, mass='64.0 amu')\n",
    "\n",
    "integrator = mm.LangevinIntegrator(300.0*unit.kelvin, 1.0/unit.picoseconds, 0.01*unit.picoseconds)\n",
    "platform = Platform.getPlatformByName('CUDA')\n",
    "simulation = Simulation(molecular_system.topology, molecular_system.system, integrator, platform)\n",
    "\n",
    "coordinates = np.zeros([1, 3], np.float32) * unit.nanometers\n",
    "simulation.context.setPositions()\n",
    "\n",
    "velocities = np.zeros([1, 3], np.float32) * unit.nanometers/unit.picoseconds\n",
    "simulation.context.setVelocities()\n",
    "\n",
    "simulation.step(1000)\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## With this library"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from uibcdf_systems import FreeParticle\n",
    "\n",
    "molecular_system = FreeParticle(n_particles=1, mass='64.0 amu')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Newtonian dynamics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from uibcdf_systems.tools import langevin\n",
    "from openmm import unit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "coordinates = np.zeros([1, 3], np.float32) * unit.nanometers\n",
    "velocities = np.zeros([1, 3], np.float32) * unit.nanometers/unit.picoseconds\n",
    "velocities[0,0] = 0.10 * unit.nanometers/unit.picoseconds\n",
    "\n",
    "molecular_system.set_coordinates(coordinates)\n",
    "molecular_system.set_velocities(velocities)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "29a119ab79f74524849bc7ceaa5685ad",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [

      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "traj_dict = langevin(molecular_system,\n",
    "                     friction=0.0/unit.picoseconds,\n",
    "                     temperature=0.0*unit.kelvin,\n",
    "                     time=0.2*unit.nanoseconds,\n",
    "                     saving_timestep=0.10*unit.picoseconds,\n",
    "                     integration_timestep=0.01*unit.picoseconds)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "dict_keys(['time', 'coordinates', 'potential_energy', 'kinetic_energy', 'box'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "traj_dict.keys()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
